person:biography.personal-details:content: Maulidiani was awarded her PhD from Universiti Putra Malaysia in 2014. Her research interests are metabolomics and natural products chemistry. Previously, she was a postdoctoral researcher at the Institute of Bioscience, Universiti Putra Malaysia from 2015-2018. She is now a lecturer in the Faculty of Science and Marine Environment, Universiti Malaysia Terengganu (former appointment was at the School of Fundamental Science (PPSA), Universiti Malaysia Terengganu). To date, she has been involved in various projects related to herbal and food metabolomics.
